{"id":"1512.03040","submitter":"Bela Bajnok","authors":"B\\'ela Bajnok","title":"Comments on Y. O. Hamidoune's Paper \"Adding Distinct Congruence Classes\"","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.NT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The main result in Y.~O.~Hamidoune's paper \"Adding Distinct Congruence\nClasses\" ({\\em Combin.~Probab.~Comput.}~{\\bf 7} (1998) 81-87) is as follows: If\n$S$ is a generating subset of a cyclic group $G$ such that $0 \\not \\in S$ and\n$|S| \\geq 5$, then the number of sums of the subsets of $S$ is at least $\\min\n(|G|, 2|S| )$. Unfortunately, argument of the author, who, sadly, passed away\nin 2011, relies on a lemma whose proof is incorrect; in fact, the lemma is\nfalse for all cyclic groups of even order. In this short note we point out this\nmistake, correct the proof, and discuss why the main result is actually true\nfor all finite abelian groups.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 9 Dec 2015 20:46:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-10"}
