ving their formation, and how this affects\nthe surface. Using many images of the same areas with different viewing angles,\nwe performed a 3-dimensional reconstruction of collimated jets, and linked them\nprecisely to their sources on the nucleus. Results.We show here observational\nevidence that the Northern hemisphere jets of comet 67P arise from areas with\nsharp topographic changes and describe the physical processes involved. We\npropose a model in which active cliffs are the main source of jet-like\nfeatures, and therefore the regions eroding the fastest on comets. We suggest\nthat this is a common mechanism taking place on all comets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Dec 2015 09:57:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 11 Dec 2015 13:14:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-02-17"}
